es out a hand from under the sheet, as he holds up a left hand and points out a scar on the left thumb, they do not speak but they weep \x{2013}They do not speak but they weep and they weep \x{2013}\x{2018}I am here because of you\x{2026}\x{2019}They weep and they weep but they still do not speak as Dr. Nakadate slowly pulls back the grey sheet, as he shows them the bleached face of a young girl, seventeen years old \x{2013}\x{2018}I am Midorikawa Ryuko of Meguro\x{2026}\x{2019}They weep and they weep but they still do not speak until Mrs. Midorikawa finally looks up from the bleached face of her daughter, from the ruined corpse of her child and cries out, \x{2018}Kodaira!\x{2019}*Inspector Kai and I stand in the corridor between the autopsy room and the mortuary and wait for Mrs. Midorikawa and her two older daughters to finish their discussions with the Kei\x{14d} staff about the funeral arrangements for her youngest daughter. Inspector Kai is smoking a cigarette. Inspector Kai is smiling. Inspector Kai is looking at his notebook, a name written three times \x{2013}Kodaira. Kodaira. Kodaira \x{2026}\x{2018}This time tomorrow,\x{2019} laughs Inspector Kai. \x{2018}This case will be closed and I\x{2019}ll be drunk\x{2026}\x{2019}Dr. Nakadate\x{2019}s assistant comes down the narrow corridor. He bows. He apologizes for interrupting our conversation. He hands me a piece of paper torn from a newspaper and says, \x{2018}This was found folded in the pocket of the skirt of the pinafore dress on your body.\x{2019}I open out the piece of newspaper. It is an advertisement \x{2013}Salon Matsu in Kanda now hiring new staff \x{2026}It is a clue, at last. It is a start, at last \x{2013}\x{2018}You never know,\x{2019} laughs Kai. \x{2018}Maybe this time tomorrow, we\x{2019}ll both be drunk\x{2026}\x{2019}I bow and I thank Dr. Nakadate\x{2019}s assistant as Mrs. Midorikawa and her two daughters step out of the mortuary room \x{2013}The arrangements have been made.Now Inspector Kai