ng Kodaira while Nishi and I were chasing ghosts out at the International Palace and the rest of my room were walking the streets of Shiba, in the heat and in the dirt \x{2013}Investigation is footwork \x{2026}\x{2018}There are some similarities with other cases,\x{2019} says the chief. \x{2018}And so these other cases are going to need to be washed again. Now I know there is a shortage of manpower so, first of all, we are going to need to see how many of these other cases match up with the various places that the suspect Kodaira has lived and worked\x{2026}\x{2019}\x{2018}And the first case is that of Abe Yoshiko\x{2026}\x{2019}Shinagawa. Shinagawa. Shinagawa \x{2026}\x{2018}You might remember that the body of a teenage girl was found by a signal operator on the thirteenth of June this year, just over two months ago now, under a burnt-out truck in the scrapyard of the Shibaura Transportation Company at 7 Hamamachi, Shiba Ward, on the ocean side of Shinagawa train station\x{2026}\x{2019}Adachi has his eyes on me \x{2026}\x{2018}The autopsy revealed that the girl had been raped and then strangled with her own neckerchief on or around the ninth of June. The investigation headquarters was set up at Takanawa police station and was led by former Chief Inspector Mori who, as you all know, is now unfortunately no longer with us\x{2026}\x{2019}Arrested and imprisoned \x{2026}\x{2018}The body was identified as that of Abe Yoshiko who was fifteen years old and attended Dai-san Kokumin Gakk\x{14d} in Hirai. However, investigations revealed she was actually in a f\x{16b}ten group with three other girls who were doing business with American soldiers. The autopsy also revealed that her last meal had consisted of macaroni and sausage, suggesting that she was being given food by American soldiers. There was also a persistent rumour that Abe had been sleeping with a uniformed officer from the Mita police station. As you may know, this officer was identified, questioned and then dismissed because of improper conduct\x{2026}\x{2019}Dismissed and disgraced \x{2026}\x{2018}However, because of the connection with the Shinch\x{16b} Gun, because of the possible involvement of American soldiers, former Chief Inspector Mori felt unable to pursue the case and so it was recorded as unsolved and the banner rolled back up \x{2013}\x{2018}The investigation officially closed.\x{2018}However, on reading through Kodaira\x{2019}s statements and cross-referencing them with unsolved crimes of a similar nature to the murder of Midorikawa and by further cross-referencing these unsolved crimes with the dates and places Kodaira is known to have lived and worked, Chief Inspector Kanehara now believes the suspect should be questioned about the murder of Abe Yoshiko in June.\x{2019}Inspector Kanehara thanks the chief. Then Kanehara says, \x{2018}Kodaira has already denied any knowledge of the murder of Abe Yoshiko. However, earlier this morning, Kodaira\x{2019}s wife inadvertently told us that Kodaira had mentioned the groups of young women who hang around the barracks and the laundry where he works. It is my hope that we will be able to find a witness who can place Kodaira in the company of Abe on or around the ninth of June this year and then Kodaira will have little choice but to confess again \x{2013}\x{2018}So our first step will be to trace the other remaining members of Abe\x{2019}s f\x{16b}ten group. Fortunately, former Chief Inspector Mori interviewed them during the course of the initial investigation and their names and addresses were verified and recorded in the case files. If Abe was familiar with Kodaira then it is also likely one or more of these girls will also have been familiar\x{2026}\x{2019}\x{2018}And also,\x{2019} adds the chief, \x{2018}there is a slight chance that one of these girls might be able to assist in the identification of the second body we found at Shiba\x{2026}\x{2019}\x{2018}Or even be that body,\x{2019} laughs Chief Inspector Adachi